I have never commented on a YouTube video before, but I just have to. The pandemic has been really hard on me emotionally and mentally. I live abroad and haven't seen my family in over a year. I'm also about to turn 30 and am having a hard time because it feels like a year of my life was stolen from me. After some pretty depressing holidays/January, I decided in February that I wanted to do something to honor my body everyday. I'd never done yoga before, but Adrienne seemed approachable and I gave this 30 day challenge a try. I've skipped some days and repeated some videos, but I'm so proud of myself for my commitment. And TODAY it finally paid off! I touched my toes for the first time IN MY ENTIRE LIFE without having to bend my knees. I loved today's practice and absolutely needed it. Thank you so much for helping me get back in touch with my body and giving me something to smile about in 2021.

A couple months ago, a guy took advantage of me, and I let him do with barely any fight. It was a long, complicated night, following weeks of manipulations that I only realised much later. Only now am I dealing with the aftermath, after it cost me what I thought was a close and strong friendship. I am constantly so overwhelmed by what happened that I can barely move, walk, or do the most simple tasks. I spend most of my days sitting down, crying, and contemplating what happened and why instead of doing the million things I should do. And the only thing that helps me through it at the moment is my boyfriend.
However, as I've done almost every day for the past 19 days, I spread my yoga mat on the floor in the morning after having had breakfast and for however long the practise lasts, I give so much needed love to my body. And it helps, so, so much. 
Thank you for those videos, Adriene. Thank you for your positive energy. Thank you for catching us when we fall. I never thought yoga would be such an important part of my life, but right now it's one of the only things that allows me to keep going. Thank you.
